This is Youtube React tutorial
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A71aqufiNtQ&t
This example uses more modern ES6 syntax

React home page: https://facebook.github.io/react/

JSX - JavaScript Syntax Extension - preprocessor step that adds XML syntax to JavaScript
Babel is a compiler that lets you write modern JavaScript code that still works in older browsers.

To install react application:
https://facebook.github.io/react/docs/installation.html
sudo npm install -g create-react-app
create-react-app NAME_OF_YOUR_APP
cd NAME_OF_YOUR_APP
npm start

This creates a basic React application and starts it.

To build for production you would run:
npm run build

